# Keys security runtime (production schemas)

**Canonical `secret_id`:** `user_secrets.id` (`user_api_keys.vault_secret_id`). Never use `user_api_keys.id` for audit/findings.

## secret_audit_log

- PK: `id` (`saudit_` prefix)
- Every write: `secret_id`, `secret_source='user_secrets'`, `tenant_id`, `user_id`, `event_type`, `ip_address`, `user_agent`
- Rotate: `previous_last4`, `new_last4`
- Agent use: `triggered_by='agent_sam'`, `terminal_session_id` when available
- Closure: `resolved=1`, `resolved_at=unixepoch()`, `resolved_notes`

Event types: `key_created`, `key_validated_pass`, `key_validated_fail`, `key_revealed`, `key_rotated`, `key_deleted`, `key_used_by_agent`

Audit is observability only — log failures to console, do not block the operation.

## security_findings

Required on insert: `id`, `tenant_id`, `source_type='api_key'`, `source_ref=secret_id`, `finding_type`, `severity`, `fingerprint`, `created_by=user_id`, `user_id`, `workspace_id`, `secret_id`

`fingerprint = sha256(tenant_id + secret_id + finding_type)` (hex)

Status: `open` → `triaged` → `fixed` | `false_positive`

On validate pass: `UPDATE security_findings SET status='fixed', resolved_at=unixepoch() WHERE secret_id=? AND tenant_id=? AND status='open'`

`metadata_json`: `{ checks, warnings, latency_ms }`

## security_shield_rules

- `tenant_id` required; `user_id` NULL = all users in tenant
- `rule_type` enum: `key_expiry_warning`, `rotation_due`, `test_failure`, `exposure_pattern`, `untested_key_age`, `null_value_registered`, `audit_anomaly`
- On trigger: `last_triggered_at=unixepoch()`, `trigger_count=trigger_count+1`
- `notify_channels`: `dashboard` → finding row; `email` → `sendPlatformEmail`

## Provisioning

`provisionIdentitySignup` must call `buildDefaultShieldRuleStatements(env, tenantId)` in its batch.

Migration `378_security_shield_rules_all_tenants.sql` seeds all existing tenants (idempotent).

## Implementation module

Use `handleKeySecurityAfterOp` from `src/core/keys-security.js` after create/validate/reveal/rotate/delete; `getUserBYOKey` fires `agent_use` audit.
